esp32 DevKitC:
http://esp-idf.readthedocs.io/en/latest/get-started/get-started-devkitc.html

esp-idf:
http://esp-idf.readthedocs.io/en/latest/get-started/index.html#get-started-setup-path

toolchain:
http://esp-idf.readthedocs.io/en/latest/get-started/esp32-setup.html


export PATH="$PATH:$HOME/esp/xtensa-esp32-elf/bin"
printenv PATH

export IDF_PATH=~/esp/esp-idf
printenv IDF_PATH

export PATH="$PATH:$HOME/esp/xtensa-esp32-elf/bin" && export IDF_PATH=~/esp/esp-idf


.profile
source .bashrc

ls /dev/tty*                or                /dev/ttyUSB0

cd ~/esp/hello_world
make menuconfig
make flash


To see if “hello_world” application is indeed running, type make monitor. This command is launching IDF Monitor application:
make monitor
or:
make flash monitor


Update:
cd /home/osk/esp/esp-idf
git pull
git submodule update --init --recursive


If you would like to use specific release of ESP-IDF, e.g. v2.1, run:
cd ~/esp
git clone https://github.com/espressif/esp-idf.git esp-idf-v2.1
cd esp-idf-v2.1/
git checkout v2.1
git submodule update --init --recursive

